revision.text:
{{Dasam Granth Sidebar}} '''33 Savaiye''' is a religious work written by [[Guru Gobind Singh]] which is included in [[Dasam Granth]], second scripture of [[Sikh]]s.<ref>Page 176, The History of Sikh Gurus, Prithipal Singh</ref> It is present after [[Sabad Patshahi 10]] and continued with [[Khalsa Mahima]].<ref>Retrieved from Pashaura Singh, Louis E. Fenech: The Oxford Handbook of Sikh Studies: Oxford University Press, 2014</ref> It explains qualities of Supreme and Khalsa. It also rejects [[Idolatry in Sikhism|Idolatry]] and various [[Hindu]] Rituals including various [[Avatar]].
==Structure== * It is situated on page 712 to 716 of Dasam Granth. * These are 33 in number, having four stanzas each. * These were written at [[Anandpur Sahib]].<ref>Retrieved Page - 6, Dasam Granth, Dr. S.S. Kapoor, Hemkunt Press</ref> *
