As of 2010, 17% of Singaporeans have '''no religious affiliation'''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/geos/sn.html |title=The World Factbook |publisher=Cia.gov |date= |accessdate=2013-09-15}}</ref> Non-religious Singaporeans are found in various ethnic groups and all walks of life in [[Singapore]]. Singapore's non-religious tend to be [[Atheism|atheists]], [[Agnosticism|agnostics]], [[Humanism|humanists]], [[Theism|theists]], [[Deism|deists]] and [[skeptics]]. Some locals affiliate with no religion, but still choose to practice traditional rituals like ancestor worship. The number of non-religious people in Singapore has risen slightly. Census reports show that those who said they have no religion rose from 13% in 1980 to 17% in 2010. In recent years, social gatherings of non-religious people have become more popular in Singapore.

Since 2005, informal atheist groups had organised social gatherings to discuss religion and secularism, and popular books on the topic from authors such as [[Richard Dawkins]] and [[Christopher Hitchens]]. One of the earliest groups was called the ''Atheist Haven'', and was formed by three Singaporeans in 2004.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/user/AtheistHavenSG |title=Singaporean Atheists |publisher=YouTube |date= |accessdate=2013-09-15}}</ref>

==Humanist Society of Singapore==

{{main|Humanist Society of Singapore}}

In 2008, the Singapore Humanism Meetup was formed as a social network of secular humanists, atheists and agnostics.<ref>{{cite web|last=Humanism |first=Singapore |url=http://sg-humanism-meetup.blogspot.com/2010/02/shm-in-news-again.html |title=Singapore Humanism Meetup: SHM reported under 'hot' section |publisher=Sg-humanism-meetup.blogspot.com |date=2010-02-21 |accessdate=2013-09-15}}</ref> In October 2010, the [[Humanist Society (Singapore)]] became the first humanist group to be gazetted as a society. Many pioneer members of the society met at gatherings organised by the Singapore Humanism Meetup.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.humanist.org.sg |title=Humanist Society (Singapore) |publisher=Humanist.org.sg |date= |accessdate=2013-09-15}}</ref>

==Affiliation==
Non-religious groups in Singapore are also linked to other non-religious networks in Southeast Asia. The Singapore Humanism Meetup, Singaporean Atheists and Humanist Society (Singapore) are listed on the Southeast Asian Atheists website.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sea-atheists.org/singapore/ |title=Singapore |publisher=SEA-Atheists.org |date=2013-07-18 |accessdate=2013-09-15}}</ref>

