'''Nggam''' ({{IPA|[ŋgam]}}) is a type of [[divination]] found among many groups in western [[Cameroon]]. Among the best documented is its practice by the [[Mambila people]] of Cameroon and [[Nigeria]], in which the actions of [[spider]]s or [[crab]]s are interpreted by the diviner. The form used by the neighbouring Yamba people was described by Gebauer in 1964 based on experience in Mbem going back to before 1939, and more recently by Hermann Gufler (1996 and 2003). The crab form has been studied in north Cameroon by Walter van Beek (2013, 2015).

==Sources ==
