In [[Aztec mythology]], '''Tlalocayotl''' (pronounced '*Tlah-low-kye-ottle') is the [[god]] of the [[East]] [[wind]].<ref>{{cite book|title=Diccionario de Mitología Nahua|editor=Biblioteca Porrúa. Imprenta del Museo Nacional de Arqueología, Historia y Etnología|authorlink=Cecilio Agustín Robelo|language=Spanish|year=1905|location=México|pages=168, 169|isbn=978-9684327955}}</ref> His brothers are [[Cihuatecayotl]], [[Mictlanpachecatl]], and [[Huitztlampaehecatl]], who personify the winds from the [[West wind|west]], [[North wind|north]], and [[South wind|south]], respectively.<ref>{{cite book|title=Diccionario de Mitología Nahua|editor=Biblioteca Porrúa. Imprenta del Museo Nacional de Arqueología, Historia y Etnología|authorlink=Cecilio Agustín Robelo|language=Spanish|year=1905|location=México|pages=168, 169|isbn=978-9684327955}}</ref>
